üõ¢Ô∏è Database Requirements
    PostgreSQL (main structured data)
        Users, profiles, posts, media, comments, notifications
        Stories, events, achievements, polls, analytics
        NFTs, transactions, DAO votes, subscriptions
    Redis (for real-time notifications / chat)
        Session management, caching, rate limiting
        Live streaming data, real-time analytics
    SQLAlchemy (with Alembic for migrations) or SQLModel
    MongoDB (optional) for unstructured or large JSON media metadata
        AI training data, search indexes, logs
    Elasticsearch (search & analytics)
        Content indexing, user search, trending topics
    InfluxDB (time-series data)
        Analytics, metrics, performance monitoring
    Neo4j (optional - graph relationships)
        Social connections, recommendations
üóÉÔ∏è Storage Requirements
    Cloud Object Storage:
        AWS S3
        Wasabi / DigitalOcean Spaces / Cloudflare R2
    Self-hosted:
        MinIO (S3-compatible) for media files if going P2P/local-first
    Decentralized Storage:
        IPFS (InterPlanetary File System)
        Arweave (permanent storage)
        Filecoin (decentralized storage network)
    CDN & Streaming:
        Cloudflare (global CDN)
        AWS CloudFront
        Live streaming: AWS IVS, Twitch API, or custom RTMP
    Backup & Archive:
        Automated backups to multiple providers
        Cold storage for old content
        User data export capabilities
üîí Security Requirements
    HTTPS via TLS cert (Let's Encrypt or Cloudflare)
    CORS protection
    CSRF protection (for sessions)
    XSS & input sanitization (e.g., DOMPurify, helmet)
    Rate limiting and abuse prevention
    2FA via email/SMS (using third-party service like Twilio)
    End-to-end encrypted chat (via WebRTC or Matrix protocol)
